value.value: Aumento de la proporción de enlaces cruzados de desoxipiridinolina a piridinolina en la orina

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Increased ratio of deoxypyridinoline to pyridinoline cross-links in urine

label.value: Increased ratio of deoxypyridinoline to pyridinoline cross-links in urine

value.value: The relative concentration of deoxypyridinoline (Dpyr) to that of pyridinoline (Pyr) cross-links in urine is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: Detection of an increased ratio of deoxypyridinoline (Dpyr) to pyridinoline (Pyr) cross-links in urine quantitated by high-performance liquid chromatography is a highly sensitive and specific test for PLOD1-related kyphoscoliotic Ehlers-Danlos syndrome. The normal ratio of Dpyr:Pyr cross-links is approximately 0.2, whereas in kyphoscoliotic EDS the ratio is approximately 6.0.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de timina en orina

definition.value: The amount of thymine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de ácido indolacético en orina
The amount of indoleacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Reducción de la actividad de la fosforilasa quinasa hepática.

Activity of phosphorylase kinase in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal. Phosphorylase kinase (PhK) has a major regulatory role in the breakdown of glycogen. The enzyme PhK comprises four copies each of four subunits, encoded by PHKA1, PHKA2, PHKB, and PHKG.

definition.value: Phosphorylase kinase (PhK) deficiency causing glycogen storage disease type IX (GSD IX) results from deficiency of the enzyme phosphorylase b kinase, which has a major regulatory role in the breakdown of glycogen. While liver biopsy or muscle biopsy was done routinely in previous years to measure PhK activity, the availability of molecular genetic testing has reduced the need for such invasive procedures.

value.value: Reducción de la actividad de la ornitina transcarbamilasa hepática
Activity or concentration of ornithine transcarbamylase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.
Aumento del nivel de ácido quinolínico en orina

The amount of quinolinic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Quinolinic acids is a pyridinedicarboxylic acid that is pyridine substituted by carboxy groups at positions 2 and 3. It is a metabolite of tryptophan.
Duplicación rectal

A developmental anomaly characterized by an additional rectum that is typically lined with intestinal mucosa with one or more cell types of the gastrointestinal tract overlying submucosa and smooth muscle layer.
Mucosa del intestino delgado adelgazada

definition.value: Abrnormal reduction in the height of the mucosa of the small intestine. The mucosa is arranged in regular circular folds (the circular valves of Kerckrin), the mucosal surface is covered with small projections called villi, which are slender, about 1.5-2 mm long projections of the mucosa into the lumen. In between the villi are the crypts. This term refers to a pathological thinning of these structures.

value.value: Hipoplasia de vesícula seminal

definition.value: A congenital anomaly characterized by underdevelopment of one or both seminal vesicles, which are the two small glands that store and produce the majority of the fluid that makes up semen.

value.value: Circunferencia abdominal fetal pequeña
The distance around the abdomen of a fetus, generally as measured by prenatal sonography, is below the lower limit of normal.

definition.value: This finding may be associated with fetal growth restriction.

value.value: Diafragma fetal aplanado

The diaphragm normally projects up into the thoracic cavity. In the presence of malformations such as enlarged lungs, the diaphragm may appear abnormally flat or even everted (with the middle of the diaphragm projecting downwards into the abdominal cavity).

definition.value: Serr Figures 1 and 2 of PMID:30319217.

value.value: Efecto copo de nieve en la cavidad amniótica.
Dense floating particles in amniotic fluid, said to resemble snowflakes. This finding can result from shedding of the epidermis in conditions such as Harlequin ichthyosis.

definition.value: See Figure 1A of PMID:33569485.

value.value: Cúspide valvular mitral engrosada

definition.value: An abnormally increased thickness of a leaflet of the mitral valve.

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos anticélulas parietales
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against parietal cell antigens.

definition.value: This finding may be observed in autoimmune gastritis.

value.value: Anti-intrinsic-Faktor-Antikörper-Positivität
Anticuerpos positivos antifactor intrínseco
Positività degli anticorpi contro il fattore intrinseco
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against intrinsic factor.

definition.value: This finding may be observed in autoimmune gastritis.

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos contra el virus de la inmunodeficiencia humana

definition.value: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV).

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos contra el virus de la polio
The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of poliovirus.
Anticuerpos positivos anti-NR2A
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the N-Methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor NR2A subunit.
Anticuerpos positivos antiestreptolisina O

definition.value: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against streptolysin O.

Antistreptolysin O (ASO) is an antibody against streptolysin O that is generally produced by Group A Streptococcus (GAS). GAS causes a diverse range of human infections, like pharyngitis, cellulitis, scarlet fever, and others. Moreover, a GAS infection can trigger postinfectious immune-mediated disorders, including acute poststreptococcal glomerulonephritis, acute rheumatic fever, and rheumatic heart disease.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la transformilasa AICAR del tejido tisular.

value.value: Concentration or activity of 5-aminoimidazole-4-carboxamide ribonucleotide formyltransferase; EC 2.1.2.3) a in a tissue is below the lower limit of normal.
Mejora con el tratamiento de reducción del ácido gástrico.

definition.value: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with an agent that reduces gastric acidity such as proton pump inhibitors, histamine receptor blockers,omeprazole, esomeprazole, dexlansoprazole, pantoprazole, lansoprazole, famotidine, or ranitidine.

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos contra el factor de coagulación

definition.value: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against a coagulation factor.

value.value: Taquifagia
Excessively rapid eating of food.

definition.value: Although there is no universally accepted definition of what constitutes excessively rapid eating, one publication states that a meal lasting less than 15 minutes represents tachyphagia. The term also comprises bolting of food, which refers to eat food so quickly that one hardly chews or tastes it.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la argininosuccinato sintetasa tisular.

Concentration of argininosuccinate synthetase (EC 6.3.4.5) in body tissues is below the lower limit of normal. Clinically, argininosuccinate synthetase is measured in the liver or in cultered skin fibroblasts.

value.value: Activity of aspartoacylase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts. Aspartoacylase (EC 3.5.1.15), also called aminoacylase-2, is an enzyme that hydrolyzes N-acetyl-L-aspartic acid (NAA) to aspartate and acetate.
Disminución de la actividad de malonil-CoA descarboxilasa en fibroblastos cultivados

value.value: Activity of malonyl-CoA decarboxylase (EC 4.1.1.9) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.
Disminución de la actividad de acil-CoA deshidrogenasa de cadena media tisular

label.value: Reduced tissue medium-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity

value.value: Concentration or activity of medium-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (EC 1.3.8.7;MCAD) in tissues is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Activity of cystathionine beta-synthase (EC 4.2.1.22) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.
Disminución de la actividad de la glucógeno fosforilasa muscular.

Activity of the enzyme glycogen phosphorylase in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. Glycogen phosphorylase (EC 2.4.1.1) is also known as amylophosphorylase, muscle phosphorylase a and b, polyphosphorylase, and myophosphorylase.
Disminución de la actividad de la 6-fosfofructoquinasa muscular.

Activity of the enzyme 6-phosphofructokinase in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. 6-phosphofructokinase (EC 2.7.1.11) is also known as phosphofructokinase I and phosphohexokinase. The PFKM gene encodes the muscle isoform of phosphofructokinase. PFK catalyzes the irreversible conversion of fructose-6-phosphate to fructose-1,6-bisphosphate and is a key regulatory enzyme in glycolysis.
Disminución de la actividad de alfa-N-acetilglucosaminidasa tisular

Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.50) below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. It is also known as alpha-acetylglucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-glucosaminidase, and alpha-D-2-acetamido-2-deoxyglucosidase.

definition.value: Pathogenic variants in the gene encoding N-alpha-acetylglucosaminidase (NAGLU) cause Sanfilippo syndrome B (mucopolysaccharidosis type IIIB).

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de succinil-CoA: 3-oxoácido-CoA transferasa en fibroblastos cultivados

label.value: Blunted aldosterone response to aldosterone suppression test

value.value: Respuesta mitigada de aldosterona a la prueba de supresión de aldosterona

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Blunted aldosterone response to aldosterone suppression test

value.value: A non-suppressible aldosterone excess, defined as an abnormal result of one of any four suppression tests. These tests use oral sodium loading, oral fludrocortisone, oral captopril, or saline infusion to suppress aldosterone secretion.

definition.value: For instance, the sral sodium loading test involves increasing sodium intake to over 200 mmol/d for 3 days and determining urinary aldosterone from the morning of day 3 to the morning of day 4. The test is abnormal if the amount of urinary aldosterone is above the upper limit of normal. An abnormal test result generally indicates primary aldosteronism.

value.value: Masa en el flanco

definition.value: An abnormal enlargement or swelling in the flank, which is the fleshy part of the side of the body between the ribs and the hip.

value.value: Quiste sinovial

definition.value: A fluid-filled sac or pouch-like mass that is a distention of a preexisting bursa in a joint, tendon sheaths or bursae. Synovial cysts contain synovial fluid and are lined by synovial membrane.

value.value: Pigmentación marrón de la conjuntiva.
Deposition of brown pigmentation in the conjunctiva.

definition.value: This feature is a manifestation of alkaptonuria.

value.value: Contractura del gastrocnemio
Limitation of simultaneous ankle dorsiflexion and knee extension during mid-stance of gait.
Adelgazamiento central de la capa nuclear externa de la retina.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Central thinning of the outer nuclear layer of the retina

label.value: Central thinning of the outer nuclear layer of the retina

value.value: Reduced thickness of the outer nuclear layer in the middle region of the retina. The outer nuclear layer (ONL) of the retina contains the nuclei of the cone and rod photoreceptors. Loss of the cellular machinery found in these nuclei causes irreparable loss of the photoreceptors and the capacity for visual function. This feature can be appreciated by directional optical coherence tomography.
Patrón ecográfico renal en sal y pimienta

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Sonographic renal salt and pepper pattern

label.value: Sonographic renal salt and pepper pattern

value.value: Heterogeneous, increased parenchymal echogenicity. This imaging appearance is caused by multiple tiny cysts smaller than or just approaching the size necessary for detection, which disrupt the echo pattern without being clearly distinguishable, and appear as white grains on renal ultrasound, mainly in a subcapsular location.

definition.value: See Figure 2 of PMID:22034641 and Figure 11 of PMID:30599104.

value.value: Agenesia del conducto venoso con drenaje intrahepático

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Ductus venosus agenesis with intrahepatic drainage

label.value: Ductus venosus agenesis with intrahepatic drainage

value.value: A form of ductus venosus agenesis in which the umbilical vein connects via the portal sinus to the portal venous system (PVS) without giving rise to the ductus venosus. In some cases an intrahepatic shunt from a portal to a hepatic vein can be detected prenatally. This variant has been reported to have a favorable prognosis.
Agenesia del conducto venoso con drenaje extrahepático y bypass hepático

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Ductus venosus agenesis with extrahepatic drainage and liver bypass

label.value: Ductus venosus agenesis with extrahepatic drainage and liver bypass

value.value: A form of ductus venosus agenesis in which umbilical vein does not connect to the portal venous system. The liver is bypassed and the umbilical vein drains into a systemic vein such as the inferior vena cava. This variant has been reported to have an unfavorable prognosis due to a presumed association with congestive heart failure and hydrops.
Aumento del nivel de D-glicérico en sangre

definition.value: The concentration of D-gyceric acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de ácido D-glicérico en líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: The concentration of D-carboxylic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Mejorado por la riboflavina

definition.value: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingestion of riboflavin (Vitamin B2).

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de interleucina 1beta en sangre

definition.value: An increased concentration of interleukin-1beta in the blood circulation.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de mieloperoxidasa de neutrófilos.
Concentration or activity of myeloperoxidase (EC 1.11.1.7) as measured in neutrophils is below the limits of normal.
Estenosis del agujero yugular

Reduction in diameter of the jugular foramen, an opening in the base of the skull that is located behind the carotid canal and is formed by the temporal bone and the occipital bone. The inferior petrosal sinus, three cranial nerves, the sigmoid sinus, and meningeal arteries pass through the jugular foramen.
Gas intestinal intramural
The presence of extraluminal gas within the bowel wall.

definition.value: In a symptomatic postoperative patient such a finding on plain radiology or computerized tomography (CT) is often viewed as a signal of impending or actual acute mesenteric ischaemia especially when associated with portal venous gas.

value.value: Retraso en el llenado gammagráfico de la vesícula biliar

Hepatobiliary scintigraphy is a nuclear imaging technique that permits evaluation of the liver and biliary system for acute and chronic cholecystitis, biliary atresia, biliary obstruction, and post-surgical biliary leak. With this investigation, a radiotracer is administered intravenously, bound to albumin, transported to the liver, and excreted into the biliary system. This term refers to a longer than normal time for the radiotracer to be visualized in the gallbladder. This finding may be a sign of chronic gallbladder disease or partial obstruction of the common bile duct.
Malformación arteriovenosa pancreática
Pancreatic arteriovenous malformation is defined as an abnormal vascular net, developed from one or more feeding arteries and enlarged early draining veins, creating an arteriovenous shunting.
